NEW YORK - Former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan has come strongly out in support of Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa during an interview with CNN s Christiane Amanpour on Thursday.Gordhan said Ramaphosa "has been extremely brave, he has spoken truth to power... and at difficult times. He has demonstrated that he is a leader of great mettle, one who would serve the country well into the future."Gordhan also told the CNN journalist that many ANC members are extremely worried about the party and that the ANC is likely to lose the 2019 elections if things continue the way they are.He also reiterated that he believed allegations of corruption in state institutions should be dealt with in a judicial inquiry.Watch the entire interview below.eNCA